{"experiment":"tinystories_final_generation","checkpoint_iteration":10000,"checkpoint_final_validation_loss":1.3442100644111634,"tokenizer_vocab_size":10000,"prompt":"Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily.","prompt_tokens":13,"max_new_tokens":320,"seed":336,"device":"cuda","candidates":[{"name":"conservative","temperature":0.6,"top_p":0.85,"generated_tokens":178,"stopped_by_eos":true,"observation":"syntactically stable but repetitive ball/balloon and up-up-up sequences"},{"name":"balanced","temperature":0.8,"top_p":0.9,"generated_tokens":146,"stopped_by_eos":true,"observation":"best entity, setting, event, and ending consistency"},{"name":"diverse","temperature":1.0,"top_p":0.95,"generated_tokens":144,"stopped_by_eos":true,"observation":"more varied wording but hall/gym drift and an unnatural phrase"}],"selected_candidate":"balanced","selected_text":"Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She was a happy girl who loved to play outside. One day, she went to the park with her mom and dad. They brought a big cooler with them. Lily was very excited to play on the swings and slide.\n\nWhile playing, Lily saw a new friend named Tim. Tim was also going to the park. They played together and had so much fun. Tim showed Lily his cooler, and they became best friends. They played all day and shared the snacks from the cooler.\n\nWhen it was time to go home, Lily and Tim said goodbye. They promised to play together again soon. Lily went home with her mom and dad, happy to have had a new friend and a fun day at the park.","deliverable_condition":"EOS was sampled before 256 generated tokens, satisfying the assignment's alternative stopping condition","factors":["temperature and top-p trade off repetition against diversity and coherence","training-token budget and TinyStories domain determine learned story templates and fluency","model capacity and the 256-token context window constrain long-range consistency"]}
